It is a perfect and hearty snack that you can prepare for your friends and family over the weekend. The dish bursts with flavour in your mouth, the thick ground beef filling is so creamy. Preparation Step 1 To make beef sandwiches, preheat 2 tablespoons of oil inside the pan. Then, add 1lb of ground beef and 1 small chopped onion, and saut√© for 7-10 minutes over medium-high heat until brown. Step 2 Season with your spice of choice for extra flavour. Step 3 Add chopped bell pepper and 1 minced garlic then cook for 3 minutes. Step 4 Add 11/4 cup of cream of mushroom soup then season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine and cook for 5 minutes. Step 5 Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheddar cheese. Brown the inside of your bun or bread rolls then add the cheesy beef mixture. Enjoy with your favourite salad, pasta or fries.